comments.body:
@mjlbach I'm not sure why, but this looks like that RUN command that's failing is due to the OCI container format not liking something there.  Can you try specifiing `--format=docker` in your build please?  ala:

`podman build -t tensorflow_container -f devel-gpu.Dockerfile --format=docker .`

That worked for me.

@mjlbach I don't know the why, but you're right the `${CUDA/./-}` seems to be throwing the build process for a OCI container for a loop.  Honestly, I can't explain that offhand, I'd expect it to be problematic for both OCI and Docker formats if this is the issue.  I don't know what that substitution is supposed to do or guard against, do you?  It looks like the value "10.1" from the CUDA arg definition is just getting dropped in and not being changed.

However, I changed that variable to `${CUDA}` it seems to work.  

Also, can you change you `SHELL` line to `CMD` instead?

If you've the time to experiment, I'd be interested in knowing the results on your end.

@nalind or @rhatdan, any thoughts?
